John Kolak wrote:
  Any tips on preventing splintering while cutting the wood panels?

      Masking tape helps the fibers from pulling out of the cut line. 
For splinterfree cut, use 20TPI Bosch T101A0,  the teeth are tapered on 
both sides, I've seen a similar Sears Craftsman blade.
